{'hadithnumber': 101, 'text': 'Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) said: “Satan comes to one of you in Salat and blows air in his bottom, so he imagines that he has realised air yet he did not. So if he gets that feeling he should not leave his prayer unless he hears the sound (of the air) or smells its odour.” .'}
{'hadithnumber': 102, 'text': 'It is originally from the Sahihain of Bukhari and Muslim as the Hadith narrated by ‘Abdullah bin Zaid.'}
{'hadithnumber': 103, 'text': 'And Muslim reported by Abu Huraira likewise.'}
{'hadithnumber': 104, 'text': '“If Satan comes to one of you and says: ‘You have nullified your ablution (by releasing air)’, let him say: ‘You have lied.” .'}
{'hadithnumber': 105, 'text': '“Let him say in his heart...”'}
{'hadithnumber': 106, 'text': 'Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) used to remove his ring when entering the lavatory. .'}
{'hadithnumber': 107, 'text': 'The  Prophet (ﷺ) on entering the lavatory used to say: \\n\\n“O Allah, I seek refuge with You from devils – males and females (or all offensive and wicked things, evil deeds and evil spirits, etc.)”'}
{'hadithnumber': 108, 'text': 'Whenever Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) went to the privy, a servant and I used to carry a skin water container and a spear, and he would cleanse himself with the water. .'}
{'hadithnumber': 109, 'text': 'Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) told me, “Take the skin water”, he then went forward till he disappeared from me and relieved himself'}
{'hadithnumber': 110, 'text': 'Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) said: “Safeguard yourselves from the two matters which cause accursing that befalls the one who relieves himself on people’s path-ways and under the shades.” .'}
{'hadithnumber': 111, 'text': 'He said: “Guard against the three things which cause curse (i.e.) defecating at the watering places, on the roadbeds and in the shades.”'}
{'hadithnumber': 112, 'text': 'Ahmad reported from Ibn Abbas (rad) that defecation is prohibited also at the place where water collects. .'}
{'hadithnumber': 113, 'text': 'At-Tabarani also narrated on the authority of Ibn ‘Umar (with a weak chain of narrators), the prohibition of relieving oneself under fruit trees and beside the bank of a flowing river.'}
{'hadithnumber': 114, 'text': 'Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) said: “When two people go together to relieve themselves they should disappear from each other and do not talk, for Allah detests that”. .'}
{'hadithnumber': 115, 'text': 'Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) said: “Nobody should touch his pennies with his right hand when urinating, and should not clean himself (from defecation or urine) using his right hand and should not breathe in the utensil (he is drinking from).” .'}
{'hadithnumber': 116, 'text': 'Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) forbade us to face the Qiblah when defecating or urinating, or to clean ourselves using the right hand, or to clean ourselves with less than three stones, or to clean ourselves with dung or a bone .'}
{'hadithnumber': 117, 'text': 'Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) “Neither face nor turn your back to the Qiblah while defecating or urinating, but turn towards the east or the west”.'}
{'hadithnumber': 118, 'text': 'The Prophet (ﷺ) said: “If anyone goes to relive himself, he should conceal himself”. .'}
{'hadithnumber': 119, 'text': 'When the Prophet (ﷺ) came out of the privy, he used to say, “Ghufranaka (O Allah! Grant me Your forgiveness)”. .'}
{'hadithnumber': 120, 'text': 'The Prophet (ﷺ) went out to answer the call of nature and asked me to bring three stones. I found two stones and searched for the third but could not find it. So I took a dried piece of dung and brought it to him. He took the two stones and threw away the dung and said, “This is a filthy thing”.'}
{'hadithnumber': 121, 'text': '“Bring me more (something other than dung)”].'}
{'hadithnumber': 122, 'text': 'Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) forbade us to use a bone or dung for cleaning and said, “These two things do not purify”. .'}
{'hadithnumber': 123, 'text': 'Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) said: “Beware of (smearing yourselves with) urine, because it is the main cause of punishment in the grave”.'}
{'hadithnumber': 124, 'text': '“Urination is the main cause of punishment in the grave”. .'}
{'hadithnumber': 125, 'text': 'Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) educated us about lavatory (manners) that we should sit on our left foot and keep erect our right foot. .'}
{'hadithnumber': 126, 'text': 'Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) said: “When one of you passes urine, he should empty his penis three times”. .'}
{'hadithnumber': 127, 'text': 'The Prophet  (ﷺ) asked the residents of Quba that what had earned them the Praise of Allah and they replied, “We use water after (cleaning ourselves with) stones.”'}
{'hadithnumber': 128, 'text': 'and its Asl (original source) is in Abu Da’ud and At-Tirmidhi and Ibn Khuzaima graded it Sahih (sound) through Abu Huraira (rad) without mentioning the “stones”.]'}
{'hadithnumber': 129, 'text': 'Allah’s Mesenger (ﷺ) said: “The water (of the ghusl) is due to the water (of sexual emission)”.'}
{'hadithnumber': 130, 'text': 'and its Asl (origin) is in Al-Bukhari.'}
{'hadithnumber': 131, 'text': 'Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) said that, “If one of you sits between her legs (of a woman) and penetrates her, Ghusl (bath) is obligatory.” .'}
{'hadithnumber': 132, 'text': '“Even if he does not ejaculate”.'}
{'hadithnumber': 133, 'text': 'Umm Sulaim, the wife Abu Talha said, “O Allah’s Messenger! Allah is not ashamed of the truth. Is a Ghusl (bath) compulsory for a woman when she has a sexual dream?” He (ﷺ) replied, “Yes! When she sees signs of liquid” .'}
{'hadithnumber': 134, 'text': 'Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) said about the precept of a woman having ejaculation during sleep like a man, “She should take a Ghusl (bath)”.'}
{'hadithnumber': 135, 'text': 'Umm Salama said, “Does this happen (to a woman)?” He (ﷺ) said: “Yes, otherwise where does the resemblance (of a child to its mother) come from?”'}
{'hadithnumber': 136, 'text': 'Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) used to take a bath from four things; after sexual intercourse, on Fridays, after extracting blood from his body and after washing a dead body.'}
{'hadithnumber': 137, 'text': 'The Prophet (ﷺ) ordered him to take a bath.'}
{'hadithnumber': 138, 'text': 'and its origin is in Al-Bukhari and Muslim.'}
{'hadithnumber': 139, 'text': 'Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) said: “Taking a bath on Friday is a must for every adult”. .'}
{'hadithnumber': 140, 'text': 'Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) said: “Whoever performs ablution on Friday has done a good thing and he who takes bath, taking bath is better  (for him).”'}
{'hadithnumber': 141, 'text': 'The Prophet (ﷺ) used to teach us the Qur’an except when he was in a state of sexual impurity. .'}
{'hadithnumber': 142, 'text': 'Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) said: “If one of you has sexual intercourse with his wife and wishes to repeat he should perform ablution between them” .'}
{'hadithnumber': 143, 'text': '“Ablution makes one active for repeating (the sexual act).”'}
{'hadithnumber': 144, 'text': 'Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) used to sleep in the state of sexual impurity without touching water. .'}
{'hadithnumber': 145, 'text': 'Whenever Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) took Ghusl (bath) after sexual intercourse, he would begin by washing his hands, then pour water with his right hand on his left hand and wash his sexual organ. He would then perform ablution, then take some water and run his fingers through the roots of the hair. Then he would pour three handfuls on his head, then pour water over the rest of his body and subsequently wash his feet.'}
{'hadithnumber': 146, 'text': 'Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) poured water over his private parts and washed them with his left hand. He then struck his hand against the earth.'}
{'hadithnumber': 147, 'text': '"And he wiped it with earth".'}
{'hadithnumber': 148, 'text': 'And in the last of this version: “I handed him a piece of cloth, but he did not take it... He started shaking the water off his hand.”'}
{'hadithnumber': 149, 'text': 'I said, "O Messenger of Allah, I am a woman who keeps her hair closely plaited. Do I have to undo them for Ghusl after sexual intercourse?" In another narration, "and after the end of menses?" He replied (ﷺ), "No, is it enough for you to throw three handfuls of water over your head."\\nRelated by Muslim.'}
{'hadithnumber': 150, 'text': 'Allah\'s messenger (ﷺ) said: "It is not permitted for a menstruating woman or one who is junub (sexually impure) to stay in the mosque."\\nRelated by Abu Dawud and Ibn Khuzaimah graded it as Sahih'}
